        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer92919826" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18433534529729124044">I won this book on Goodreads first-reads giveaway. I really wanted to love this book, especially after having read the previous reviewer&apos;s glowing words. But, it fell flat for me. I thought that the idea was truly original and it is obvious that the author has a definite passion for her subject. However, it lacked depth, and often (especially the first half of the book) I felt like I was reading a script rather than a novel. This is a story of three women who were all negatively affected by the </span>
  <span id="freeText18433534529729124044" style="display:none">I won this book on Goodreads first-reads giveaway. I really wanted to love this book, especially after having read the previous reviewer's glowing words. But, it fell flat for me. I thought that the idea was truly original and it is obvious that the author has a definite passion for her subject. However, it lacked depth, and often (especially the first half of the book) I felt like I was reading a script rather than a novel. This is a story of three women who were all negatively affected by the fact that their spouses were gay males whose entries into marriage was a farce. I wanted to feel sorry for the women and I am sure that this would be a devastating experience. Unfortunately, the author, Krome, didn't help me get to know the women of the story as people. I was inundated with their bad experience, but was never really able to connect with anyone in the novel. <br />There is some value in the novel. It opened my eyes into a world which I was not aware. I wish that Krome had written a philosophical/sociological nonfiction book about this phenomena rather than a novel. In fact, I would encourage her to do so. I have the feeling that a nonfiction writing would be a better way to get her point across to the right audience. </span>
  <a data-text-id="18433534529729124044" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


